    {
      "datasource": null,
      "description": "A trace-first journey map for Pi sessions. Use the filters to narrow logs by session, agent, or agent run, then open matching Tempo traces to inspect the waterfall.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "# ObservMe Trace Journey\n\nFollow how one Pi request travels through the system: `session → agent run → turn → LLM → tool/bash → subagent spawn → wait/join → branch/compaction`. Prometheus panels show aggregate flow and latency, Loki panels show the ordered event trail, and Tempo search opens the full trace waterfall.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.1.0",
      "title": "Trace journey map",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus"
      },
      "description": "Currently active ObservMe agent runtimes, counted from the active runtime gauge instead of the started/shutdown counter estimate.",
